FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1780945878
OL,3,CMajor report recommends complete ban
OL,4,Con sunbeds
OL,6,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,7,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,8,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,9,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,11,FThe report highlights a study which
OL,12,Ffound that banning commercial sunbeds
OL,13,Fwould be cost-effective and would lead
OL,14,Fto fewer cases of skin cancer, fewer
OL,15,Fskin cancer deaths and ease the burden
OL,16,Fon the NHS.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1780945878
OL,3,CMajor report recommends complete ban
OL,4,Con sunbeds
OL,6,FThere are currently three countries
OL,7,Fthat have banned commercial sunbeds:
OL,8,FIran, Brazil and Australia. These bans
OL,9,Fapply to commercial sunbeds but home
OL,10,For private use remains possible.
OL,12,FCommenting on the report, Dr Tamara
OL,13,FGriffiths, president of the British
OL,14,FAssociation of Dermatologists, said:
OL,15,F"There is now a consensus that sunbed
OL,16,Fregulation and enforcement in the UK
OL,17,Fare not strong enough.
OL,19,F"The British Association of
OL,20,FDermatologists believes that the case
OL,21,Ffor a ban is already strong.
OL,26,@wD@AOU{D@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
